s.\r\n\r\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process we are confident that we can find the right nanny for your family.','Nanny Screening Process','','publish','open','open','','nanny-screening-process','','','2012-12-02 01:09:07','2012-12-02 01:09:07','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=164',0,'page','',0),(165,1,'2012-11-23 03:17:52','2012-11-23 03:17:52','What is the screening process for nannies joining Bumble Bees Nannies?\n\nAt Bumble Bees Nannies, all nanny applicants are required to submit their updated resume, as well as an application form. If nannies have Early Childhood qualifications and/or at least 3 years experience, they will be asked to come into the agency to discuss their experiences, qualifications, philosophies on raising children and why they finished with their last employer. During this process we also discuss their interests, hobbies and their reason for becoming a nanny. I find this information important to make a great match with a  family.\n\nBumble Bees Nannies also checks:\n<ul>\n	<li>References</li>\n	<li>Valid First Aid and CPR certification</li>\n	<li>Up to date Police Check</li>\n	<li>Drivers License details and/or passport, birth certificate</li>\n	<li>Working status if they are not a Canadian citizen</li>\n</ul>\nWhile going through their resume/CV, we look for any loopholes/gaps that they have missed and find out why they have missed out certain areas.\n\nWith Bumble Bees Nannies doing this process, it will eliminate the amount of work you need to do and the amount of nannies calling you and coming into your home doing interviews. It can be confusing interviewing multiple candidates, so let Bumble Bees Nannies do all the work finding the right nanny for you. Bumble Bees Nannies aims for families to only interview 2-4 nannies which we think will suit all your needs and requirements.\n\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees Nannies requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process, we are confident that we can find the r','Nanny Screening Process','','inherit','open','open','','164-revision','','','2012-11-23 03:17:52','2012-11-23 03:17:52','',164,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/164-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(166,1,'2012-11-23 03:19:00','2012-11-23 03:19:00','','Screening Process','','publish','open','open','','166','','','2012-12-03 02:48:17','2012-12-03 02:48:17','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=166',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(167,1,'2012-11-23 03:26:45','2012-11-23 03:26:45','<h4>Nanny Pay Scale</h4>\r\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a <a title=\"Childcare Options\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/childcare-options/#live-out-nannies\">Live-out</a> nanny:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Part-time nannies ( less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12-$20 an hour</li>\r\n	<li>35-40 hour week- between $ 450-550 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n	<li>40-50 hour week- between $500-$650 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny’s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n\r\n<h4>Tax Information</h4>\r\n\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nTo pay your nanny you will need to apply for a Business number with The Canadian Revenue Agency. This is a very simple process. Once this has been done you can either use The Canadian revenue agency or use Bumble Bees Nannies’ new Nanny Payroll service. \r\n\r\n<h4>Bumble Bees Nannies Payroll</h4>\r\n<div class=\"payroll-table\">\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is now offering a new service: Nanny Payroll. We will start this service in January 2013. This service will reduce all your worry with paying your nanny.\r\n\r\nFor $300 per year, we\'ll help take care of:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n<li>Calculating your nanny\'s gross net pay</li>\r\n<li>Nanny direct deposit</li>\r\n<li>Pay the CRA remittances on time on your behalf</li>\r\n<li>Issue a T4 at year end</li>\r\n<li>Issue a Record of Employment for your  nanny at the end of employment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','publish','open','open','','nanny-pay-scale-and-tax-information','','','2012-12-02 02:06:15','2012-12-02 02:06:15','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?page_id=167',0,'page','',0),(168,1,'2012-11-23 03:26:25','2012-11-23 03:26:25','Nanny Payscale\n\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours. Live-out and Live-in nannies receive a different salary because the living costs (accommodation and food) are taken into account for Live-in nannies.\n\nAn estimated cost of a Live-out nanny:\n\nPart-time nannies (less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12 - $20 an hour.\n\n35-40 hour week - between $450 - $500 per week, net.\n\n40-50 hour week - between $500 - $600 per week, net.\n\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny\'s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\n\n<h4>Tax Information</h\n\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\n\nThis can be done through the Canadian Revenue Agency or with Bumble Bees Nannies.\n\n&nbsp;','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision','','','2012-11-23 03:26:25','2012-11-23 03:26:25','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(169,1,'2012-11-23 03:26:4