 you and the other family decide to work together and decide to use Bumble Bees Nannies, then I will use your application forms to look for a nanny for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"controls\"><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-sharing\';\">Families With A Shared Nanny</button><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-looking\';\">Families Looking For A Shared Nanny</button></div>','Nanny Share Family Finder','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-14','','','2012-11-30 02:55:19','2012-11-30 02:55:19','',115,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/115-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(278,1,'2012-12-01 22:06:15','2012-12-01 22:06:15','<em>Sometimes sharing a nanny might be the best option for your family – a more affordable alternative!</em>\r\n\r\n<em>When two families come  together to share a nanny for their children, this is called a “Nanny Share”. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Option 1</em></strong><em>: The nanny can care for both sets of children on all days Monday- Friday. There is usually only 1 child from each family in this option. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Option 2</em></strong><em>: The nanny alternates between caring for one family’s children on one day, and the other family’s children on the other days. </em>\r\n\r\n<em>With a nanny share, the families involved should have the same philosophies on parenting, routines, discipline, etc. In most nanny shares, the involved families have one child each. Nanny share nannies usually work between 45- 50 hours per week.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Many families would like to alternate between the two houses, 1-2 weeks in each home. If this is done it could unsettle the children and disrupt their routine. Consistency is very important for young children.   It can also disrupt the nannies routine and schedule especially when children’s items are forgotten eg winter hats and gloves, sunscreen, bottles.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Points to consider when starting a Nanny Share</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>The household where the children will be based will need to have an extra sleeping area and bed (pack and play)</em>\r\n\r\n<em>The cost of children’s groceries will need to be halved ie. milk, food, diapers, wipes</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Transport for two children, whether it be two car seats or a double stroller if needed. <strong></strong></em>\r\n\r\n<em>Transporting your child’s bottles every morning and afternoon or buying an extra set for the other house<strong></strong></em>\r\n\r\n<em>For the house that is having the children that there will be more toys, bottles, plates, cups in your home. <strong></strong></em>\r\n\r\n<em>When the nanny gets vacations which would work for both families.  Most nannies get between 2 weeks’ vacation and the days between Christmas and New Year.  For the two weeks I always recommend that the families pick one week and the nanny picks the other week to make it fair.<strong></strong></em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Positives of being a part of a Nanny share</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Sharing the cost of the nanny ages/ salary</em>\r\n\r\n<em>The children learn to socialize with children their own age</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Develop a close friendship with the other child</em>\r\n\r\n<em>The children learn to share and participate with each other.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class=\"controls\"><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-sharing\';\">Families With A Shared Nanny</button><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-looking\';\">Families Looking For A Shared Nanny</button></div>','Nanny Share Family Finder','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-15','','','2012-12-01 22:06:15','2012-12-01 22:06:15','',115,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/115-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(279,1,'2012-12-01 22:08:46','2012-12-01 22:08:46','Sometimes sharing a nanny might be the best option for your family – a more affordable alternative!\r\n\r\nWhen two families come together to share a nanny for their children, this is called a “Nanny Share”.\r\n\r\n<strong>Option 1:</strong> The nanny can care for both sets of children on all days Monday- Friday. There is usually only 1 child from each family in this option.\r\n<strong>Option 2:</strong> The nanny alternates between caring for one family’s children on one day, and the other family’s children on the other days.\r\n\r\nWith a nanny share, the families involved should have the same philosophies on parenting, routines, discipline, etc. In most nanny shares, the involved families have one child each. Nanny share nannies usually work between 45- 50 hours per week.\r\n\r\nMany families would like to alternate between the two houses, 1-2 weeks in each home. If this is done it could unsettle the children and disrupt their routine. Consistency is very important for young children. It can also disrupt the nannies routine and schedule especially when children’s items are forgotten eg winter hats and gloves, sunscreen, bottles.\r\n\r\n<h4>Points to consider when starting a Nanny Share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>The household where the children will be based will need to have an extra sleeping area and bed (pack and play)</li>\r\n	<li>The cost of children’s groceries will need to be halved ie. milk, food, diapers, wipes</li>\r\n	<li>Transport for two children, whether it be two car seats or a double stroller if needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Transporting your child’s bottles every morning and afternoon or buying an extra set for the other house</li>\r\n	<li>For the house that is having the children that there will be more toys, bottles, plates, cups in your home.</li>\r\n	<li>When the nanny gets vacations which would work for both families. Most nannies get between 2 weeks’ vacation and the days between Christmas and New Year. For the two weeks I always recommend that the families pick one week and the nanny picks the other week to make it fair.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Positives of being a part of a Nanny share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Sharing the cost of the nanny ages/ salary</li>\r\n	<li>The children learn to socialize with children their own age</li>\r\n	<li>Develop a close friendship with the other child</li>\r\n	<li>The children learn to share and participate with each other.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-sharing\';\">Families With A Shared Nanny</button><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-looking\';\">Families Looking For A Shared Nanny</button>','Nanny Share Family Finder','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-16','','','2012-12-01 22:08:46','2012-12-01 22:08:46','',115,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/115-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(280,1,'2012-12-02 02:13:43','2012-12-02 02:13:43','<h4 id=\"live-out-nannies\">Live-Out Nannies</h4>\nLooking for someone to look after your child/children weekdays while you are at work? A nanny may be the best option for you.\n\nA nanny can be full time, part time or temporary. Nannies are generally sole charge, meaning that they are the only caregiver present with your child/ren.\n\nFull-time Live-out nannies work around 8-10 hours a day, Monday - Friday. With a Live-Out Nanny, additional babysitting outside of the standard schedule can be provided by agreement or contract (at additional cost).\n\nBumble Bees Nannies have the qualifications you are looking for, including Early Childhood Education credits and years of childcare experience. A nanny can take care of a broad range of responsibilities, including just about everything related to your children:\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n	<li>Playing and Entertaining</li>\n	<li>Creating stimulating environments</li>\n	<li>Making sure that everything is age appropriate</li>\n	<li>Organizing play dates, sports and activities</li>\n	<li>Cleaning the children\'s rooms/bathrooms and toys</li>\n	<li>Helping with homework</li>\n	<li>Cooking for the children and associated kitchen cleanup</li>\n	<li>Organizing and taking children to their doctors/dentist/hair appointments</li>\n	<li>Children\'s laundry</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"mothers-help\">After School Care</h4>\nBumble Bees Nannies can provide quality After School Care. They will pick up your children from school, organize after school activities, help children with their homework, cook dinner and make sure all information from school is given to parents.\n\nWe usually try and place daycare teachers who have morning jobs or university students who are completing their degrees, ECE diplomas, Nursing students, psychology that are looking to work as After School Nannies to earn extra money.\n<h4 id=\"nanny-share\">Nanny Share</h4>\nCheck our <a title=\"Nanny Share Family Finder\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/nanny-share/\">Nanny Share</a> section for more information.\n\n&nbsp;','Childcare Options','','inherit','open','open','','197-autosave','','','2012-12-02 02:13:43','2012-12-02 02:13:43','',197,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/197-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(281,1,'2012-11-30 04:32:43','2012-11-30 04:32:43','<h4>Live-Out Nannies</h4>\r\nLooking for someone to look after your child/children weekdays while you are at work? A nanny may be the best option for you.\r\n\r\nA nanny can be full time, part time or temporary. Nannies are generally sole charge, meaning that they are the only caregiver present with your child/ren.\r\n\r\nFull-time Live-out nannies work around 8-10 hours a day, Monday - Friday. With a Live-Out Nanny, additional babysitting outside of the standard schedule can be provided by agreement or contract (at additional cost).\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies have the qualifications you are looking for, including Early Childhood Education credits and years of childcare experience. A nanny can take care of a broad range of responsibilities, including just about everything related to your children:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Playing and Entertaining</li>\r\n	<li>Creating stimulating environments</li>\r\n	<li>Making sure that everything is age appropriate</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing play dates, sports and activities</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning the children\'s rooms/bathrooms and toys</li>\r\n	<li>Helping with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Cooking for the children and associated kitchen cleanup</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing and taking children to their doctors/dentist/hair appointments</li>\r\n	<li>Children\'s laundry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Mother\'s Help</h4>\r\nNeed an extra pair of hands to help you with your children during the day? A Bumble Bees Mother\'s Helper can work hours similar to a nanny or a part time or be temporary. A mother\'s help is someone who is newer to childcare, with more limited experience. They are not left in sole charge of children for extended periods - they are there to look after the children alongside the parents, or alone with the children for a limited time when the parents are busy. A mother\'s helper can help with household chores such as emptying the dishwasher, folding laundry and grocery shopping. The Mother\'s help duties can vary and will be agreed upon and clarified by contract, by both mother\'s help and employer. Mother\'s helpers generally do not provide housekeeping services.\r\n<h4>After School Care</h4>\r\nBumble Bees Nannies can provide quality After School Care. They will pick up your children from school, organize after school activities, help children with their homework, cook dinner and make sure all information from school is given to parents.\r\n\r\nWe usually try and place daycare teachers who have morning jobs or university students who are completing their degrees, ECE diplomas, Nursing students, psychology that are looking to work as After School Nannies to earn extra money.\r\n\r\nNanny Share\r\n\r\nCheck our <a title=\"Nanny Share Family Finder\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/nanny-share/\">Nanny Share</a> section for more information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Childcare Options','','inherit','open','open','','197-revision-3','','','2012-11-30 04:32:43','2012-11-30 04:32:43','',197,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/197-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(282,1,'2012-12-01 22:26:39','2012-12-01 22:26:39','','After School Care','','publish','open','open','','childcare-optionsafter-school-care','','','2012-12-03 02:19:09','2012-12-03 02:19:09','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=282',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(283,1,'2012-12-01 22:27:05','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2012-12-01 22:27:05','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/?p=283',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(284,1,'2012-11-30 04:29:11','2012-11-30 04:29:11','<h4>Why Use A Nanny Agency?</h4>\r\n\"Bumble Bees Nannies will find the perfect nanny for your family. I personally evaluate the childcare needs of your family and together we\'ll find the best nanny with the right experience and personality to care for your little ones. Qualified nannies have so much to offer, helping children have a great start in life. From teaching children as they play, preparing them for school, giving them love and attention, Bumble Bees Nannies will use all their knowledge and experience to fulfill the children\'s needs, providing a healthy, educational and safe environment\"\r\n\r\n- <strong>Richelle Assenberg</strong>, owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUsing Bumble Bees Nannies will help you find your perfect nanny. Using our agency means that you don\'t have to do all the work which is involved in hiring someone to work with children; answering the many phone calls you will receive of interested caregivers looking for work or responding to all the emails, searching the internet daily, checking resumes and conducting many interviews. This work can take a lot of time up, let Bumble Bees Nannies do this all for you.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is alos registered with Toronto Police so we can conduct Vulnerable Person\'s Police Checks with written permission from the applicants.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is the place to go in Toronto when searching for excellence in childcare services for your family\r\n<h4>Positives Of Having A Nanny</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Your child will receive more attention from the caregiver - one on one</li>\r\n	<li>Your child will develop a close bond with the nanny quicker than in a daycare</li>\r\n	<li>Your children will be able to go on trips on a regular basis, weekly or bi-weekly; parks, zoo, science centre, swimming</li>\r\n	<li>Consistency and routine of being with another child and nanny builds trust and stability</li>\r\n	<li>You are able to come home and your children have had their dinner and are ready to spend quality time with you. No daycare runs and then having to go home and still cook dinner for your children and get them ready for bed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>What Differentiates Us?</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>We will guide you through the process in finding the right childcare solution for your family</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies conducts face-to-face meetings with families, getting to know our clients and their childcare needs to facilitate the perfect nanny match</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies recommends have trials that are 2-4 days long to see if the nanny suits your family and to see if they fit in. This reduces the chance of nanny\'s not working out</li>\r\n	<li>3 Month Trials: If your nanny decides to leave, Bumble Bees Nannies will attempt to find a suitable replacement free of charge</li>\r\n	<li>Bumble Bees Nannies will provide full support for families throughout the 3 Month Trial</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Customized, personal service</strong> - simply the best for your family!</li>\r\n</ul>','Families','','inherit','open','open','','154-revision-10','','','2012-11-30 04:29:11','2012-11-30 04:29:11','',154,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/154-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(285,1,'2012-11-27 03:58:31','2012-11-27 03:58:31','If you have the right experience, personality and knowledge, we can help you find your perfect job as a LiveIn Nanny, Live-Out Nanny, Mother\'s Helper, After School care or Nanny-share, permanent or temporary, full time or part time. If you are newly qualified or wish to gain further experience, there are many opportunities to explore, such as being a mother\'s helper or even babysitting.\r\n\r\nIf you have the right qualifications and experience, and you successfully complete a series of checks and the interview process, you will be registered as a Bumble Bees Nannies Childcare Professional.\r\n\r\n\"Welcome to Bumble Bees Nannies. Being a nanny is a fulfilling and professional career choice, working with children on a one to one level, watching them grow up and develop into little adults. You help them through their stages of development and support them in their everyday choices as they get older. I am here to help you find a great family to work with so you also can enjoy these great experiences like I have. Through my seven years of nanny experience I can offer you extra advice and help when deciding a family/job, from interview advice to finding childcare groups in your neighbourhood. I want to help nannies, and share my knowledge and skills - like others have done for me\"\r\n\r\n- <strong>Richelle Assenberg</strong>, owner of <strong>Bumble Bees Nannies</strong>','Caregivers','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-3','','','2012-11-27 03:58:31','2012-11-27 03:58:31','',35,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/35-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(286,1,'2012-12-01 22:09:12','2012-12-01 22:09:12','Sometimes sharing a nanny might be the best option for your family – a more affordable alternative!\r\n\r\nWhen two families come together to share a nanny for their children, this is called a “Nanny Share”.\r\n\r\n<strong>Option 1:</strong> The nanny can care for both sets of children on all days Monday- Friday. There is usually only 1 child from each family in this option.\r\n<strong>Option 2:</strong> The nanny alternates between caring for one family’s children on one day, and the other family’s children on the other days.\r\n\r\nWith a nanny share, the families involved should have the same philosophies on parenting, routines, discipline, etc. In most nanny shares, the involved families have one child each. Nanny share nannies usually work between 45- 50 hours per week.\r\n\r\nMany families would like to alternate between the two houses, 1-2 weeks in each home. If this is done it could unsettle the children and disrupt their routine. Consistency is very important for young children. It can also disrupt the nannies routine and schedule especially when children’s items are forgotten eg winter hats and gloves, sunscreen, bottles.\r\n\r\n<h4>Points to consider when starting a Nanny Share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>The household where the children will be based will need to have an extra sleeping area and bed (pack and play)</li>\r\n	<li>The cost of children’s groceries will need to be halved ie. milk, food, diapers, wipes</li>\r\n	<li>Transport for two children, whether it be two car seats or a double stroller if needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Transporting your child’s bottles every morning and afternoon or buying an extra set for the other house</li>\r\n	<li>For the house that is having the children that there will be more toys, bottles, plates, cups in your home.</li>\r\n	<li>When the nanny gets vacations which would work for both families. Most nannies get between 2 weeks’ vacation and the days between Christmas and New Year. For the two weeks I always recommend that the families pick one week and the nanny picks the other week to make it fair.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Positives of being a part of a Nanny share</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Sharing the cost of the nanny ages/ salary</li>\r\n	<li>The children learn to socialize with children their own age</li>\r\n	<li>Develop a close friendship with the other child</li>\r\n	<li>The children learn to share and participate with each other.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"controls\">\r\n<button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-sharing\';\">Families With A Shared Nanny</button><button class=\"btn\" onclick=\"document.location=\'families-looking\';\">Families Looking For A Shared Nanny</button>\r\n</div>','Nanny Share Family Finder','','inherit','open','open','','115-revision-17','','','2012-12-01 22:09:12','2012-12-01 22:09:12','',115,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/115-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(287,1,'2012-11-30 04:29:39','2012-11-30 04:29:39','What is the screening process for nannies joining Bumble Bees Nannies?\r\n\r\nAt Bumble Bees Nannies, all nanny applicants are required to submit their updated resume, as well as an application form. If nannies have Early Childhood qualifications and/or at least 3 years experience, they will be asked to come into the agency to discuss their experiences, qualifications, philosophies on raising children and why they finished with their last employer. During this process we also discuss their interests, hobbies and their reason for becoming a nanny. I find this information important to make a great match with a  family.\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies also checks:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>References</li>\r\n	<li>Valid First Aid and CPR certification</li>\r\n	<li>Up to date Police Check</li>\r\n	<li>Drivers License details and/or passport, birth certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Working status if they are not a Canadian citizen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhile going through their resume/CV, we look for any loopholes/gaps that they have missed and find out why they have missed out certain areas.\r\n\r\nWith Bumble Bees Nannies doing this process, it will eliminate the amount of work you need to do and the amount of nannies calling you and coming into your home doing interviews. It can be confusing interviewing multiple candidates, so let Bumble Bees Nannies do all the work finding the right nanny for you. Bumble Bees Nannies aims for families to only interview 2-4 nannies which we think will suit all your needs and requirements.\r\n\r\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees Nannies requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process, we are confident that we can find the right nanny for your family.','Nanny Screening Process','','inherit','open','open','','164-revision-3','','','2012-11-30 04:29:39','2012-11-30 04:29:39','',164,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/164-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(288,1,'2012-11-27 03:30:21','2012-11-27 03:30:21','Bumble Bees Nannies will email resumes for you to look at without charge. If you would like to begin interviewing nannies, then there will be a $100 + HST, one-off booking fee.\r\n\r\nThis is non-refundable, but it is deducted from your placement fee. The booking fee will be invoiced and is due before any interviews are set to take place.\r\n\r\nWhen you have decided on a nanny, we will assist you in drawing up a contract which both parents and nanny will sign. At this time, we will invoice you for 50% of the balance of the placement fee (minus the $100 booking fee). The balance of the placement fee is due no later than 3 days before the nanny\'s start date.\r\n<div class=\"fee-table\">\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$1,000 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Full time (Over 30 hours a week) Permanent Placement. If two families come to Bumble Bees Nannies for a Nanny Share, then the placement fee is half each</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$700 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Part time (Under 29 hours a week) Permanent Placement</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$700 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Per family for a Nanny Share when Bumble Bees Nannies finds the other family as well as the nanny</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$500 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Two-Month Temporary Placemment</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$500 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">After School Care</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fee-row\">\r\n<div class=\"cost\">$50 + HST</div>\r\n<div class=\"description\">Register with the Emergency Babysitting</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Fee Structure','','inherit','open','open','','190-revision-4','','','2012-11-27 03:30:21','2012-11-27 03:30:21','',190,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/190-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(289,1,'2012-12-02 00:48:33','2012-12-02 00:48:33','What is the screening process for nannies joining Bumble Bees Nannies?\r\n\r\nAt Bumble Bees Nannies, all nanny applicants are required to submit their updated resume, as well as an application form. If nannies have Early Childhood qualifications and/or at least 3 years experience, they will be asked to come into the agency to discuss their experiences, qualifications, philosophies on raising children and why they finished with their last employer. During this process we also discuss their interests, hobbies and their reason for becoming a nanny. I find this information important to make a great match with a  family.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div4\"></div>\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies also checks:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>References</li>\r\n	<li>Valid First Aid and CPR certification</li>\r\n	<li>Up to date Police Check</li>\r\n	<li>Drivers License details and/or passport, birth certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Working status if they are not a Canadian citizen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhile going through their resume/CV, we look for any loopholes/gaps that they have missed and find out why they have missed out certain areas.\r\n\r\nWith Bumble Bees Nannies doing this process, it will eliminate the amount of work you need to do and the amount of nannies calling you and coming into your home doing interviews. It can be confusing interviewing multiple candidates, so let Bumble Bee