dates so let Bumble Bees do all the work,  finding the right nanny for you. Bumble Bees aims for families to only interview 2-4 nannies which we think will suit all your needs and requirements.\n\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process we are confident that we can find the right nanny for your family.','Nanny Screening Process','','inherit','open','open','','164-autosave','','','2012-12-02 01:09:06','2012-12-02 01:09:06','',164,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/164-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(291,1,'2012-12-02 01:07:05','2012-12-02 01:07:05','At Bumble Bees Nannies all nanny applicants are required to submit their updated resume as well as an Application form. If nannies have Early Childhood qualifications and/or at least 3 years’ experience they will be asked to come into the agency to discuss their experiences, qualifications, philosophies on raising children, why they stopped working with their last employer.   During this process we also discuss their interests, hobbies, and their reason for becoming a nanny. I find this information important to make a great match with a family.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"divider div4\"></div>\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies also checks:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>References</li>\r\n	<li>Valid First Aid and CPR certification</li>\r\n	<li>Up to date Police Check</li>\r\n	<li>Drivers License details and/or passport, birth certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Working status if they are not a Canadian citizen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhile going through their resume/CV, we look for any loopholes/gaps that they have missed and find out why they have missed out certain areas.\r\n\r\nWith Bumble Bees Nannies doing this process, it will eliminate the amount of work you need to do and the amount of nannies calling you and coming into your home doing interviews. It can be confusing interviewing multiple candidates, so let Bumble Bees Nannies do all the work finding the right nanny for you. Bumble Bees Nannies aims for families to only interview 2-4 nannies which we think will suit all your needs and requirements.\r\n\r\nNannies who meet all Bumble Bees Nannies requirements will then be matched with appropriate families. With our extensive nanny screening process, we are confident that we can find the right nanny for your family.','Nanny Screening Process','','inherit','open','open','','164-revision-5','','','2012-12-02 01:07:05','2012-12-02 01:07:05','',164,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/164-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(292,1,'2012-12-02 01:22:10','2012-12-02 01:22:10','<strong>1. What your family needs from a childcare professional</strong>\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n	<li>Do you need someone to help solely with your children or also run errands?</li>\n	<li>Do you need an extra pair of hands around the house to help with the children?</li>\n	<li>Does the child care professional need to be active and young at heart?</li>\n	<li>How many years experience would you like the nanny to have?</li>\n	<li>Is a driver necessary for school runs, after school activities or play dates?</li>\n	<li>Full or part time?</li>\n	<li>Would both parents be at work during the day so you need a very qualified nanny, with great communication skills?</li>\n	<li>Would you like your caregiver to have the same interests as you or your children?</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>2. Shall I hire a Live-In or Live-Out Nanny?</strong>\n\n<strong>Live-In Nanny</strong>:\n\nThe salary of a live-in nanny is lower than a live-out nanny because the food and accommodation is taken into account. If the nanny lives with you, you need provide a bedroom, living area, bathroom and theyneed to have access to the kitchen and most areas of the house, they become a part of the family and a close bond with the nanny and family is usually developed quite quickly.\n\nA negative side to consider is the lack of privacy after hours and in weekends.\n\nUnfortunately Bumble Bees Nannies does not offer Live-in Nannies.\n\n<strong>Live-Out Nanny</strong>: Families choose live-out nannies if there is a lack of space for a nanny to live with the family and the family want to keep their privacy, especially in the weekends and after hours. Most of the qualified and experienced nannies are Live-out nannies; they have their own homes, families to go back to at the end of each day.\n\n<strong>3. Contact Bumble Bees Nannies via Email or Phone</strong>\n\nFill in an <a title=\"Family Registration Form\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/family-registration/\">online form</a> with the basic details of your family needs and then we will contact you with further questions. Or email <a href=\"mailto:richelle@bumblebeesnannies.com\">Bumble Bees Nannies</a> directly with a brief message on what you are looking for and we will contact you as soon as possible.\n\n<strong>4. Application Forms</strong>\n\nOnce this has been done, we will call you to discuss your needs and answer any questions you may have. An application form will then be emailed to you that you will need to fill out and email back. We use this to write job descriptions for the nannies to read and to help us get a sense of what you are looking for to make the match.\n\nAt Bumble Bees we like to conduct face to face meetings with families at a local café during the day so we can get a better idea of what the family needs are so we can match you with a nanny. We not only match by family requirements but also by personalities and interests.\n\n<strong>5. Nanny Search</strong>\n\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has received the application form, we will start looking for nannies who suit your needs and wants. During this process, we will keep in regular contact with you, updating you on the progress.\n\n<strong>6. Interview Process</strong>\n\nOnce Bumble Bees Nannies has found nannies that we think will suit what you are looking for, you will be emailed resumes to read through as well as our own personal thoughts about why the nanny would suit your family. If you are interested in the nannies, an interview will be setup. During this stage, a <a title=\"Fee Structure\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/fee-structure/\">Booking Fee</a> will be invoiced to you.\n\nOnce you have had your interviews and have decided on a  nanny, a Nanny Trial will be arranged. This is so that the family and nanny get to know each other before a job offer is made.\n\n<strong>7. Nanny Trials</strong>\n\nRichelle recommends a trial so that the family can see the nanny interact with the children and family and for the nanny to see how the parents interact with their children. It should be a relaxing time, so the nanny can settle in and feel comfortable. It is recommended that the family pay the nanny for this time, minimum wage and last between 3-4 hours or to 4-5 days, depending on how well you feel it is going.\n\n<strong>8. Final Steps</strong>\n\nOnce you have decided on a nanny, then we can make a job offer to the nanny. If she accepts, then Bumble Bees Nannies will write a contract for you and the nanny can start.\n\nYou will receive a more descriptive \'Step-by-Step\' when we contact you so you know in detail how it works.','Families Step-By-Step','','inherit','open','open','','187-autosave','','','2012-12-02 01:22:10','2012-12-02 01:22:10','',187,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/187-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(293,1,'2012-11-30 04:31:44','2012-11-30 04:31:44','<strong>1. What your family needs from a childcare professional</strong>\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li> Do you need someone to help solely with your children or also run errands?</li>\r\n	<li>Do you need an extra pair of hands around the house to help with the children?</li>\r\n	<li>Does the child care professional need to be active and young at heart?</li>\r\n	<li>How many years experience would you like the nanny to have?</li>\r\n	<li>Is a driver necessary for school runs, after school activities or play dates?</li>\r