=\"payroll\">\nBumble Bees Nannies is now offering a new service: Nanny Payroll. We will start this service in January 2013. This service will reduce all your worry with paying your nanny.\n\nFor $300 per year, we\'ll help take care of:\n<ul class=\"styled\">\n<li>Calculating your nanny\'s gross net pay</li>\n<li>Nanny direct \n','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-autosave','','','2012-12-02 02:04:50','2012-12-02 02:04:50','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(308,1,'2012-11-23 03:27:06','2012-11-23 03:27:06','The required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours. Live-out and Live-in nannies receive a different salary because the living costs (accommodation and food) are taken into account for Live-in nannies.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a Live-out nanny:\r\n\r\nPart-time nannies (less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12 - $20 an hour.\r\n\r\n35-40 hour week - between $450 - $500 per week, net.\r\n\r\n40-50 hour week - between $500 - $600 per week, net.\r\n\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny\'s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n<h4>Tax Information</h4>\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nThis can be done through the Canadian Revenue Agency or with Bumble Bees Nannies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-3','','','2012-11-23 03:27:06','2012-11-23 03:27:06','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(309,1,'2012-12-02 02:00:49','2012-12-02 02:00:49','<h4>Nanny Pay Scale</h4>\r\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a <a title=\"Childcare Options\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/childcare-options/#live-out-nannies\">Live-out</a> nanny:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Part-time nannies ( less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12-$20 an hour</li>\r\n	<li>35-40 hour week- between $ 450-550 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n	<li>40-50 hour week- between $500-$650 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny’s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n\r\nTax Information\r\n\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nThis can be done through the Canadian Revenue Agency or with Bumble Bees Nannies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-4','','','2012-12-02 02:00:49','2012-12-02 02:00:49','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(310,1,'2012-12-02 02:05:40','2012-12-02 02:05:40','<h4>Nanny Pay Scale</h4>\r\nThe required minimum wage is set as $10.25, as of March 2010, with time and a half for every hour over 44 hours.\r\n\r\nAn estimated cost of a <a title=\"Childcare Options\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/families/childcare-options/#live-out-nannies\">Live-out</a> nanny:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Part-time nannies ( less than 35 hours a week) are paid an hourly wage. Depending on qualifications and experience between $12-$20 an hour</li>\r\n	<li>35-40 hour week- between $ 450-550 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n	<li>40-50 hour week- between $500-$650 net a week ($14-$16 an hour)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese prices are all dependent on the nanny’s qualifications and experience. It can also increase if there are three children.\r\n\r\n<h4>Tax Information</h4>\r\n\r\nParents are employers and are responsible for paying the nanny\'s taxes. This includes federal and provincial tax, Canada\'s Pension Plan (CPP) and Employers Insurance (EI).\r\n\r\nTo pay your nanny you will need to apply for a Business number with The Canadian Revenue Agency. This is a very simple process. Once this has been done you can either use The Canadian revenue agency or use Bumble Bees Nannies’ new Nanny Payroll service. \r\n\r\n<h4>Bumble Bees Nannies Payroll</h4>\r\n<div class=\"payroll\">\r\nBumble Bees Nannies is now offering a new service: Nanny Payroll. We will start this service in January 2013. This service will reduce all your worry with paying your nanny.\r\n\r\nFor $300 per year, we\'ll help take care of:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n<li>Calculating your nanny\'s gross net pay</li>\r\n<li>Nanny direct deposit</li>\r\n<li>Pay the CRA remittances on time on your behalf</li>\r\n<li>Issue a T4 at year end</li>\r\n<li>Issue a Record of Employment for your  nanny at the end of employment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n','Nanny Pay Scale and Tax Information','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-5','','','2012-12-02 02:05:40','2012-12-02 02:05:40','',167,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/167-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(311,1,'2012-12-01 22:25:10','2012-12-01 22:25:10','<h4 id=\"live-out-nannies\">Live-Out Nannies</h4>\r\nLooking for someone to look after your child/children weekdays while you are at work? A nanny may be the best option for you.\r\n\r\nA nanny can be full time, part time or temporary. Nannies are generally sole charge, meaning that they are the only caregiver present with your child/ren.\r\n\r\nFull-time Live-out nannies work around 8-10 hours a day, Monday - Friday. With a Live-Out Nanny, additional babysitting outside of the standard schedule can be provided by agreement or contract (at additional cost).\r\n\r\nBumble Bees Nannies have the qualifications you are looking for, including Early Childhood Education credits and years of childcare experience. A nanny can take care of a broad range of responsibilities, including just about everything related to your children:\r\n<ul class=\"styled\">\r\n	<li>Playing and Entertaining</li>\r\n	<li>Creating stimulating environments</li>\r\n	<li>Making sure that everything is age appropriate</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing play dates, sports and activities</li>\r\n	<li>Cleaning the children\'s rooms/bathrooms and toys</li>\r\n	<li>Helping with homework</li>\r\n	<li>Cooking for the children and associated kitchen cleanup</li>\r\n	<li>Organizing and taking children to their doctors/dentist/hair appointments</li>\r\n	<li>Children\'s laundry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"mothers-help\">Mother\'s Help</h4>\r\nNeed an extra pair of hands to help you with your children during the day? A Bumble Bees Mother\'s Helper can work hours similar to a nanny or a part time or be temporary. A mother\'s help is someone who is newer to childcare, with more limited experience. They are not left in sole charge of children for extended periods - they are there to look after the children alongside the parents, or alone with the children for a limited time when the parents are busy. A mother\'s helper can help with household chores such as emptying the dishwasher, folding laundry and grocery shopping. The Mother\'s help duties can vary and will be agreed upon and clarified by contract, by both mother\'s help and employer. Mother\'s helpers generally do not provide housekeeping services.\r\n<h4 id=\"after-school-care\">After School Care</h4>\r\nBumble Bees Nannies can provide quality After School Care. They will pick up your children from school, organize after school activities, help children with their homework, cook dinner and make sure all information from school is given to parents.\r\n\r\nWe usually try and place daycare teachers who have morning jobs or university students who are completing their degrees, ECE diplomas, Nursing students, psychology that are looking to work as After School Nannies to earn extra money.\r\n\r\n<h4 id=\"nanny-share\">Nanny Share</h4>\r\n\r\nCheck our <a title=\"Nanny Share Family Finder\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/nanny-share/\">Nanny Share</a> section for more information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Childcare Options','','inherit','open','open','','197-revision-4','','','2012-12-01 22:25:10','2012-12-01 22:25:10','',197,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/197-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(312,1,'2012-11-28 03:12:54','2012-11-28 03:12:54','Here are the job vacancies, with the text that goes along describing the jobs...','Job Vacancies','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-6','','','2012-11-28 03:12:54','2012-11-28 03:12:54','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/21-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(313,1,'2012-12-02 02:34:22','2012-12-02 02:34:22','Here is the Job Vacancies description, with the text that goes along describing the jobs...\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Full Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/full-time/\">Full Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Part Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/part-time/\">Part Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"After School Care\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/after-school-care/\">After School Care</a>','Job Vacancies','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-7','','','2012-12-02 02:34:22','2012-12-02 02:34:22','',21,'http://localhost/bumblebees/blog/21-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(314,1,'2012-12-02 02:35:03','2012-12-02 02:35:03','Here is the Job Vacancies description, with the text that goes along describing the jobs...\r\n\r\n<a class=\"btn\" title=\"Full Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/full-time/\">Full Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Part Time\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/part-time/\">Part Time</a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"After School Care\" href=\"http://localhost/bumblebees/job-vacancies/after-school-care/\">After School Care</a>','Job Vacancies','','inh